From 0b92a7d83b2b4ee16979e9d5fed8c50c72365d35 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 22:14:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Two-stage analysis: Haiku OCRs image slides, Opus analyzes
 text-only

- config.yaml: add vision.ocr_model: claude-haiku-4-5
- claude_client.py: _ocr_images_sync runs Haiku on image blocks; _analyze_sync
  feeds OCR text to Opus text-only (no images sent to Opus). Falls back to
  combined call if OCR fails. image_text back-filled from OCR stage.
- prompts.py: IMAGE_OCR_SYSTEM_PROMPT + build_image_ocr_prompt; build_user_prompt
  accepts image_text kwarg and injects it as a labeled section.

